# Observability agent (@observability)

**Owns:** Read-only APIs for probe history, status transitions, and aggregate monitor status.

## Key paths

- `app/routers/status.py` — `GET /api/v1/status/summary`
- `app/routers/monitors.py` — **history routes only**: `GET /{monitor_id}/checks`, `GET /{monitor_id}/transitions`
- `app/schemas/checks.py` — `CheckResponse`, `TransitionResponse`, paginated list types, `StatusSummary`

## Boundaries

- Read-only at the HTTP layer; writes happen in @check-engine.
- Uses `monitor_repo.get_monitor` for existence checks; do **not** own CRUD (@monitor-api).
- List queries live in check/transition repos — add filters/indexes with @check-engine if write path affected.

## Conventions

- Paginate with `PaginationDep`; return total + limit + offset.
- Map DB rows to response models in the route layer; keep repos returning `TypedDict` rows.

## Verify

`uv run pytest tests/test_api_history.py -v`
